  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Summarization for Vulnerable Families Homes Headed by Women in Gaza Strip</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Four years after the 2014 war in the Gaza Strip, an estimated 56,440 housing units still need repair works, and a total of 24,300 housing units do not meet 50% or more of core criteria for standard housing conditions. Difficult living conditions are particularly exacerbated in the summer season as many shelters are not adapted to provide adequate protection and comfort. The Summarization of Vulnerable Families&#x2019; Homes Headed by Women in Gaza Strip project aims to enhance the access of vulnerable families headed by women to adequate housing conditions through basic upgrading services according to shelter minimum standards. The shelter upgrade will prepare housing units for the summer season  and improve the overall living conditions by providing increased thermal comfort, personal safety, improved privacy, improved hygiene and life with dignity considering age and gender. 
The project will target 80 women-headed households living in substandard housing conditions. The households have been identified as needing urgent upgrading ahead of the summer season through previous SIF projects. The project will contribute to reducing the number of the 2,800 households in substandard housing condition headed by divorced or widowed women identified by the shelter cluster. Ultimately, it will decrease the overall caseload of households (HHs) needing upgrades in the Gaza Strip. 
SIF has already extensive experience in house repair projects, as it has been implementing directly two shelter projects with direct funds from SIF in addition to another shelter project funded by OCHA since 2016, targeting 229 HHs in 2016-2017 and 2017-2018 targeting 229 HHs in total. The 2017-2018 project finished in February 2018 and SIF is seeking to continue repair works with vulnerable households it has identified in previous assessments.</narrative>
  </description>
